### Test JWT Authentication Flow

### 0. User Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "username": "exampleuser",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 1. User Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Get User Profile (with token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3. Get User Info (with token from login)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/info
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Refresh Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accessToken": "{{accessToken}}",
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

### 5. Update Profile (email/username/phone/address are optional; send only what you want to change)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/profile
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "newmail@example.com",
  "username": "newusername",
  "phone": "+90 555 123 45 67",
  "address": "Istanbul, Turkiye"
}

### Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7001
@accessToken = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE
@refreshToken = YOUR_REFRESH_TOKEN_HERE
